		<title>13The Miners Strike</title>
		<content> The main reasons for the strike was   
 the threatened closure of many pits   
 and the demand for a pay rise.        
 The loss of coal and money was 70     
 pound a tonne which is:-              
 70*250,000=17,500,000 pounds being the
 value of the coal lost.               
 The running cost of the mine is       
 approximately 23 million pounds and   
 they have an electricity bill of      
 100,00 ponds a month.This then was    
 saved.The strike lasted from March 13 
 1984 to the beginning of March 1985.  
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
